data.name: Bacon Carbonara
data.quickTastyDescription: A creamy, savory pasta dish featuring crispy bacon and a rich egg-based sauce that comes together in no time.
detailedCookingInstructions: Cook spaghetti according to package instructions until al dente.
While the pasta is cooking, chop the bacon and garlic.
In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat and add the bacon. Cook until crispy, then add the garlic for the last minute of cooking.
In a bowl, whisk together the eggs, grated Parmesan cheese, black pepper, and a pinch of salt.
Once the pasta is cooked, reserve a cup of pasta water and drain the rest. Add the pasta to the skillet with the bacon, off the heat.
Quickly pour the egg mixture over the hot pasta, stirring quickly to create a creamy sauce. If the sauce is too thick, add a bit of reserved pasta water until desired consistency is reached.
